[36m(TaskRunner pid=722912)[0m The denominator is zero when \( (x + 3)(x - 2) = 0 \). This gives us the solutions \( x = -3 \) and \( x = 2 \). These are the points where the function is undefined, and they are potential vertical asymptotes.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=722912)[0m 
